EventArgsInstrumentDiscovered Members

EventArgsInstrumentDiscovered Class  Constructors  Methods  Properties  See Also

When an instrument is discovered, the instrument discovery event handler is called. This is Event Arguments object which contains information about discovered instrument, or error information if an exception occurred.

The following tables list the members exposed by the EventArgsInstrumentDiscovered type.

Properties
Name Description
DiscoverState Gets or sets the state of the discovery system.
InstrumentId Gets the identifier of the instrument.
JSRException If an error occurs during discovery, and exception might get generated. In this case this field will contain that exception object. If no error occurred, this will be null.
NotifyType Gets or sets the type of the event that occurred
PulserReceiverIds Gets an array of identifiers of the pulser receivers contained within the discovered instrument. Important: Some instrument plugins may fire this event with this array having length 0 to signify that no instruments were found. This does not apply to USB, but does apply to the DPR series instruments.
